  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR852881.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">For the two-disk system, which of the following quantities must remain constant between the time that Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is dropped on Disk <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and the time that the two disks begin rotating with the same speed?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The kinetic energy only</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
